# FootballScanningAI — Cursor rules

## PBA V2 — Solo vs partner

- **Default scope:** For training activities (Dribble or Pass, Away From Pressure, One Touch Passing, Two-Minute Test, etc.), implement **new** behavior, timing, and UI **only in solo mode** unless the user explicitly asks to change partner / relay / coach display behavior.

## PBA V2 — Two-Minute Critical Scan (Display)

- **Overlay during ballVisible:** The overlay text (status/coaching copy at the bottom) must fade out or reduce opacity during `ballVisible` so the ball is the focus. Keep this behavior when changing the display view.

## Layout and scrolling

- **Opening screen only:** The intro screen (“Do you know what you'll do before the ball gets to you?”) may use `ScrollView` on small devices so all content is visible. Other PBA/flow screens stay non-scrolling unless explicitly required.
